Author: Alan Warsaw

Publish Time: 2023-03-03T05:56:24+00:00

Update Time: 2023-03-03T16:58:06+00:00

Images: ['[21kanker4-800x445.jpg](https://www.redspark.nu/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/21kanker4-800x445.jpg)']

Tags: ['CPI (maoist)', 'CPI(maoist)', 'Gadchiroli', 'Gadchiroli district', 'India', 'Maharashtra', 'Maharashtra State', 'Naxal', 'naxalites', 'naxals', 'police', 'PPW in India']

Categories: ['India', "People's War"]

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Redspark/2023-03-03T05-56-24-00-00/21kanker4-800x445.jpg)**Gadchiroli District, March 3, 2023:** A squad of 15-20 armed Naxalitesconducted a raid on a bridge construction site Maharashtra's Gadchirolidistrict, setting fire to three vehicles engaged in the project, police saidon Friday.

According to police the incident took place on Thursday evening at around 8pmin Ettapali area in Gadchiroli district. This is the second such incident tooccur in the district this week, they said.

"Armed Naxalites torched one JCB machine, one Poclain machine and one mixermachine vehicle engaged in the construction of a bridge on Puraslagondi-Alengaroad," a police official said. A probe is being carried out into the incident,he said.

On Monday night, suspected Naxalites had torched a mixer machine vehicleengaged in road construction work in Botanpundi-Visamundi road in thedistrict.

