Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-03-03T17-31-42-03-00/foto-ato.jpg)Students refuse to pay tariffs. Photo: Database and

![Print friendly, pdf & email](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-03-03T17-31-42-03-00/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxOTQiIGhlaWdodD0iMzAiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCAxOTQgMzAiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIHN0eWxlPSJmaWxsOiNjZmQ0ZGI7ZmlsbC1vcGFjaXR5OiAwLjE7Ii8+PC9zdmc+)This Wednesday, March 1st students of the Federal University of Ouropreto(UFOP)They held a manifestation against the imposition of the collection of energy in university housing by the university. Students have agitation in front of the University Restaurant(R.U.)from UFOP and the Emguida walked in act to the Dean of Community Affairs and Estudantis(Work)where they put themselves and pressured the pro-rectorarindicating that the university pay the electricity accounts and improvement conditions of infrastructure in the houses.

The institution wants to oblige students to bear the cost of energy in houses and transfer the title of the accounts of the CNPJ of university to the CPF of one of the students. The university subsidizes on average $ 250, insufficient amount to pay the electricity bill of housing with 20 students per home.

21-year-old Beatriz and a university village resident was participating in damnifestation and declares: “We received a _e-email_ and at no time was a dialogue to learn about the situation, we really received aviolence”. The _e-mail_ in question contained an office sent on the 13th defender to the students who boycotted the blackmail of the university serecuse to pay and said that “the resolution […] still defines […] warning from breach of the duties described in art. 28 and ** Loss of Law Avaga ** in case of recurrence in the warning penalty, in the period of a one. ”UFOP has been aroused with the energy costs of the university village since its inception in 2017 until August 2022, however due to the lack of resources now imposes on students. According to Natália de Souza Lisboa, the dean of Pracem interviews and, “[..] We will pay back to the electricity of all ascas during the pandemic, it is as if we made an exchange because as R.U. It was not working a value left was left that made it possible to do this budget, with the return of face -to -face activities in March of the past year, from R.U. And our budget [getting] less and less did not have to do that. ”

![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-03-03T17-31-42-03-00/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDI0IiBoZWlnaHQ9Ijc2OCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDEwMjQgNzY4Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBzdHlsZT0iZmlsbDojY2ZkNGRiO2ZpbGwtb3BhY2l0eTogMC4xOyIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)PRACE, Portrait of Student Assistance in Brazil. Photo: Database

UFOP also states that non -payment of bills is preventing walking the implementation of photovoltaic energy at the university, “we have two casas who are pending payment and these two houses are preventing a project of energy sufficiency and economy from the entire university,” says Pro -Rector. Students interviewed by and, through the Information Access Law, found that in reality the university has a Novalor debt of R $ 227,088.00 with the Energy Company of Minas Gerais(CEMIG)Until it has a date, incongruous amount with the debt of only two houses.

![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-03-03T17-31-42-03-00/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDI0IiBoZWlnaHQ9IjQ1NCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDEwMjQgNDU0Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBzdHlsZT0iZmlsbDojY2ZkNGRiO2ZpbGwtb3BhY2l0eTogMC4xOyIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)UFOP True with Cemig. Photo: Reproduction.

The students have already scheduled a new demonstration for next Wednesday 08/03 and claim without blinking, "we will resist resisting."

