# Remove Marcos's Cha-Cha, Democratic Organizational Call

Author: Philippine Revolution Web Central

Publish Time: 2023-03-03T98:00:00-04:00

Modified Time: None

Description: Democratic organizations are preparing to oppose the purpose of changing the 1987 Constitution today in Congress. It is estimated to be passed on March 6 in the third and final hearing

Images: ['[charter-change-labanan-1024x683.jpg](https://philippinerevolution.nu/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/charter-change-labanan-1024x683.jpg)']

Categories: ["People's Struggles", 'Politics']

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Philippine Revolution Web Central/2023-03-03T98-00-00-04-00/charter-change-labanan-1024x683.jpg )Democratic organizations are preparing to oppose the 1987 Constitution that is now being hired in Congress. House Resolution No. 6 is estimated to be presented on March 6 on the third and final hearing. 6, calls for the Constitutional Convention to change the Constitution.

"Is Cha-cha answering the country's problem?" Asked by Renato Reyes, general secretary of the town. "No. The crisis is even worse as foreign companies enter, and to extend the role of the ruling class. Foreigners and few will benefit from Cha-cha. They are the harm of our country."

The town called the plan as "Marcos Cha-cha" because his allies were pushed to the Chamber. In the final report, more than 200 congressmen support the resolution. "It also follows Marcos' policy it is advisable to open the economy to foreigners," Reyes said.

Its changes in economic provisions will further favor the ruling class and will provide additional advantages to foreign monopoly capitalists aimed at increasing and taking advantage of the country's economy, according to the town. "Even if the Constitution is replaced, if political dynasties are still sitting, nothing will change," he said.

The Alliance of Concerned Teachers also opposed the plan. "Thechacha will allow the politicians from the dynastic clans or families of landlords to the landlords of large corporations," the group said. This is in line with the expression of the terms of national and local officials from five years and allowing the re -running presidential and vice president.

Reyes mocked Marcos for pretending to be "not a priorida" of Cha-cha but "I see you in the Galawan" of his allies in Congress.

He calls on the Filipino people, do not allow Marcos Cha-cha.

News Source: [https://philippinerevolution.nu/angbayan/ibasura-ang-cha-cha-ni-marcos-panawagan-ng-mga-demokratikong-organisasyon/](https://philippinerevolution.nu/angbayan/ibasura-ang-cha-cha-ni-marcos-panawagan-ng-mga-demokratikong-organisasyon/)

