"Whose economy?" asked Sonny Africa of the bird foundation. "It is a great deal of wages to the workers," he said, and the only cause it brings is to the increasing income of the rich.

In the 2012-2021 Decade, according to Africa, workers' productivity increased by 42%, while only 18% raised wages. The values of wages have dropped by 5%. Also, during this time, the top 1,000 corporations in the country rose 68%, and 89% of the 40 -rich Filipino.

Jerome Adonis, General Secretary of the May Uno, Sibalisacan, called a "liar and cheaters" in a video message on March 1.

"That's not true," Adonis emphasized. "In fact, it can even help the Filipino wages increase." He explained that if the wages were raised, the Filipino workers would buy a purchase, especially the most basic needs. About 70% -80% of workers' wages go for food, he said.

Cebu workers, on the other hand, challenge Balisacan to live with the wages of workers.

"It is easy for Secretary Balisacan to say that because he is not a minor pay," said Jaime Lagawan, head of the father-Sugbo-KMU. "It's nice to try to live at a minimum of ₱ 435 per day in Central Visayaso even ₱ 570 per day at NCR." Paglinawan insisted that workers' wages were justified, especially after the Central Bank announced that the inflation could be hit by 9.3%.

